the patent leather kid is a 1927 silent film which tells the story of a boxer who &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; at fighting outside the ring ... particularly for the united states once it enters world war i. eventually , he is drafted , is shipped overseas , and performs a heroic act , which results in his being severely wounded . it stars richard barthelmess , molly o'day , lawford davidson , matthew betz and arthur stone . the movie was adapted by gerald c. duffy ( titles ) , winifred dunn , casey robinson ( uncredited ) and adela rogers st. johns from the story by rupert hughes . it was directed by alfred santell . it was nominated for the academy award for best actor ( richard barthelmess ) .